PN,40307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1780575067
OL,3,CMan convicted of murder after stabbing
OL,4,Cpartner to death in fit of rage
OL,6,FIn 2024, George had angrily turned on
OL,7,FMs Rook at Glastonbury Festival after
OL,8,Fgetting into a drunken row with one of
OL,9,Ftheir friends.
OL,11,FMs Rook said in her letter that
OL,12,F"something inside of me snapped", and
OL,13,Fshe wrote to her partner: "I couldn't
OL,14,Fdeal with our misunderstandings
OL,15,Fanymore.
OL,17,F"I couldn't deal with feeling like I
OL,18,Fcouldn't be myself in case I said
OL,19,Fsomething that upset you.
OL,26,@tD@AOUtD@`O]uD@[OUyD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1780575067
OL,3,CMan convicted of murder after stabbing
OL,4,Cpartner to death in fit of rage
OL,6,F"However hard I tried, I seemed to
OL,7,Fmake you angry."
OL,9,FMs Rook, a respected charity worker
OL,10,Fwho is the daughter of a retired Old
OL,11,FBailey judge, set out that she felt
OL,12,F"lonely" in the relationship and
OL,13,Funable to be true to herself.
OL,15,FIn another note that she had written
OL,16,Fto herself, Ms Rook described sitting
OL,17,Fin the spare room while trying to
OL,18,Favoid a bout of George's anger over
OL,19,Fdomestic chores.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@PO]tD@AOUtD@HO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G8/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1780575067
OL,3,CMan convicted of murder after stabbing
OL,4,Cpartner to death in fit of rage
OL,6,F"You are raging downstairs, emptying
OL,7,Fthe bins with fury, the bins I've not
OL,8,Femptied, the mess I've created", she
OL,9,Fwrote.
OL,11,F"I don't want to be around you ` you
OL,12,Fare so unkind to me.
OL,14,F"It is the third time in three days
OL,15,Fyou gaslight me and shouted me down.
OL,17,F"Mostly I don't want you hurting me
OL,18,Fanymore."
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@_O]sD@AOUvD@AOUyD@AOUzD@IO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1780575067
OL,3,CMan convicted of murder after stabbing
OL,4,Cpartner to death in fit of rage
OL,6,FWhen she was killed, Ms Rook had told
OL,7,FGeorge they should separate and made
OL,8,Fit clear he should move out of their
OL,9,Fhome in Dumont Road, Stoke Newington.
OL,11,FGeorge, an electrician, claimed at
OL,12,Ftrial that he was not short-tempered,
OL,13,Fand attempted to place the blame for
OL,14,Fthe stabbing on Ms Rook, suggesting he
OL,15,Fhad "lost it" when she pushed him in
OL,16,Fthe face.
OL,26,@wD@EOUwD@MO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G10/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40311
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1780575067
OL,3,CMan convicted of murder after stabbing
OL,4,Cpartner to death in fit of rage
OL,6,FHowever, Ms Rook's friends and family
OL,7,Fgave evidence to show that George had
OL,8,Fa "short fuse" and had shown himself
OL,9,Fto be quick to anger, while Ms Rook
OL,10,Fdescribed herself as "walking on
OL,11,Feggshells" around him.
OL,13,FIn February 2023, she had tearfully
OL,14,Ftold her father, Judge Peter Rook,
OL,15,Fthat she was considering leaving
OL,16,FGeorge, calling him a bully and
OL,17,Ffearing "he would never change".
OL,26,@pD@COUpD@NO]rD@VOUsD@JO]yD@IOUyD@_O]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G11/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40312
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1780575067
OL,3,CMan convicted of murder after stabbing
OL,4,Cpartner to death in fit of rage
OL,6,FJust days before her death, Ms Rook
OL,7,Fleft her sister a message after she
OL,8,Fand George had argued and she
OL,9,Fconcluded the relationship was "not
OL,10,Ftenable".
OL,12,F"I fear there will be some more wrath
OL,13,Fto come", she said, revealing it is
OL,14,F"not a nice place to be".
OL,16,F"I will get through this and will be
OL,17,Fstronger for it out the other side",
OL,18,Fshe said as she signed off the
OL,19,Fmessage, on June 1 2025.
OL,26,@qD@`OUrD@HO]tD@AOUuD@HO]vD@AOUvD@XO]xD@
OL,26,AAOUyD@cO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G12/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40313
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1780575067
OL,3,CMan convicted of murder after stabbing
OL,4,Cpartner to death in fit of rage
OL,6,FBut in a sign of Ms Rook's kind
OL,7,Fnature, the court also heard evidence
OL,8,Fthat she intended to give #50,000 to
OL,9,FGeorge to help him find a new home and
OL,10,Fharboured hopes that he would continue
OL,11,Fto join her on Rook family holidays in
OL,12,Fthe future.
OL,14,FIn a ruling to withdraw George's right
OL,15,Fto claim loss of self-control as a
OL,16,Fdefence to murder, Mr Justice
OL,17,FConstable KC said the evidence had
OL,18,Frevealed that he is prone to "becoming
OL,19,Fextremely and disproportionately angry
OL,20,Fand aggressive, often at minor or
OL,21,Fpetty things".
OL,26,@zD@^OU}D@MO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G13/15
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40314
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1780575067
OL,3,CMan convicted of murder after stabbing
OL,4,Cpartner to death in fit of rage
OL,6,F"The evidence was overwhelming," he
OL,7,Fsaid.
OL,9,F"It came from direct testimony from
OL,10,Fwitnesses who had both experienced
OL,11,Fthat anger directly, and to whom it
OL,12,Fwas regularly reported by Annabel
OL,13,FRook."
OL,15,FHe set out that the only possible
OL,16,Fconclusion from the evidence was that
OL,17,FGeorge was capable of "unreasonable
OL,18,Fflashing rage anger", and the murder
OL,19,Fof his partner had come during an
OL,20,F"extreme loss of temper".
OL,26,@nD@AOUnD@`O]qD@AOUuD@FO]yD@WOUzD@TO]|D@
OL,26,AAOU|D@XO]
